refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
stringfalseoci_server_version resourceconnection
Returns a string with the Oracle Database version and available options

  &reftitle.examples;



    oci_server_version example


<?php

$conn = oci_connect("hr", "hrpwd", "localhost/XE");
echo "Server Version: " . oci_server_version($conn);

// Displays:
// Server Version: Oracle Database 11g Enterprise Edition Release 11.2.0.1.0 - 64bit Production
// With the Partitioning, OLAP, Data Mining and Real Application Testing option

oci_close($conn);

?>

&reftitle.notes;



  In PHP versions before 5.0.0 you must use ociserverversion instead.
  This old name still can be used.  However it is deprecated and not recommended.
